=E5=87=BA=E4=BA=86BBA=EF=BC=88Branch By Abstraction=EF=BC=89</p>
<ol>
<li>Introduce an abstraction over the core bits of the big thing you=E2=80=
=99re going to change and commit</li>
<li>Update all the bits of code that were formerly using the thing directly=
 to use it via the new abstraction and commit</li>
<li>Make a second implementation of the abstraction, with unit tests that s=
pecifically test its core functionality and commit</li>
<li>Update all the code from (2) to use the new implementation (still via t=
he abstraction)* and commit</li>
<li>Deprecate the first implementation (or skip to 6 if you don=E2=80=99t w=
ant a respectful grace period).</li>
<li>Delete the first implementation (its proven there is no need for you to=
 go back).</li>
<li>Remove the abstraction (if it is inelegant).</li>
</ol>
